AF^2 &= \frac{(x + \frac{1}{4}) \cdot \left(\frac{25(x - 49/4)}{(4x - 49)^2}\right)}{x + \frac{5\sqrt{x - 49/4}}{2x - 49}} \\
&= \frac{(t^2 + \frac{1}{4}) \cdot \left(\frac{25t^2}{(4t^2 + 1)^2}\right)}{t^2 + \frac{5t}{2t^2 + 1}} \\
&= \frac{25t^4 + 5t^2}{16t^4 + 40t^2 + 1} \\
&= \frac{5t^2(5t^2 + 1)}{(4t^2 + 1)^2}.
\end{align*}
Substituting back in for $t$, we get
\[AF^2 = \frac{5(R^2 - 49/4)(5R^2 - 196)}{(4R^2 - 49)^2}.\]Therefore, $m+n = 5 + 196 = \boxed{201}$.

